Class WebhookEventProvider<T extends RuntimePlatform,C>

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JsonWebhookEventProvider

    public abstract class WebhookEventProvider<T extends RuntimePlatform,C>
extends RuntimeEventProvider<T>
    A specialised RuntimeEventProvider that handles HTTP requests sent by the JarvisServer.

    This class defines primitives to handle raw HTTP request contents, manipulate the parsed content, and provides an utility method that checks if the WebhookEventProvider accepts a given contentType.

      • handleParsedContent

        protected abstract void handleParsedContent(C parsedContent,
                                            org.apache.http.Header[] headers)
        Handles the parsed request content and headers.

        This method embeds the request content management that creates the associated EventInstance. The parsedContent parameter is set by an internal call to parseContent(Object).

        Parameters:
        parsedContent - the parsed request content to handle
        headers - the HTTP headers of the received request
        See Also:
        parseContent(Object)

      • handleContent

        public final void handleContent(Object content,
                                org.apache.http.Header[] headers)
        Handles the raw HTTP request content and headers.

        This method parses the provided content and internally calls handleParsedContent(Object, Header[]) to create the associated EventInstances.

        This method is part of the core API and cannot be reimplemented by concrete subclasses. Use handleParsedContent(Object, Header[]) to tune the request content processing.

        Parameters:
        content - the raw HTTP request content to handle
        headers - the HTTP headers of the received request
        See Also:
        parseContent(Object), handleParsedContent(Object, Header[])

      • getHeaderValue

        protected String getHeaderValue(org.apache.http.Header[] headers,
                                String headerKey)
        Returns the Header value associated to the provided headerKey.

        This method is an utility method that can be called by subclasses' handleParsedContent(Object, Header[]) implementation to retrieve specific values from the request Headers.

        Parameters:
        headers - the array of Header to retrieve the value from
        headerKey - the Header key to retrieve the value of
        Returns:
        the Header value associated to the provided headerKey if it exists, null otherwise
